name: Minneapolis, May 2020 | #1
description:
Minneapolis, May 2020 | #1
Civil unrest at E Lake Street and Hiawatha Avenue. 

The cops took over the intersection, relieving the very worried looking, but peaceful National Guardsmen. 

Without any communication, the cops started launching tear gas and rubber bullets into the crowd of protesters. 

Some of the gas canisters got tossed back at them. Not the one that got me, though.
